description: Maximal value of d(x) (the number of divisors of x, A000005) if the binary order (see A029837) of x, the value g(x) = n.
comments: g(x) <= n can be replaced by g(x) = n.
links: Giovanni Resta, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..250 (based on A002182 b-file)
example: In the range of g(x) <= 5, the values of d(x) can be: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8 of which 8 is the maximal, so a(n) = a(g(x)) = 8.
author: _Labos Elemer_
